Novels as Iain M. Banks

Much of Banks&#039;s science fiction deals with a vast interstellar civilisation, the Culture, which he has developed in some detail over the course of six novels and a number of short stories.

    * Consider Phlebas (1987)
    * The Player of Games (1988)

His other, non-Culture, science fiction novels are:
